This course is designed for students who want to enhance the efficient use of the body as a vehicle for expression.

The goal is to unfold how dance can be decolonized by connecting with vernacular practices in the African-Brazilian diaspora, such as Capoeira. The three techniques deployed in this course are the Flying Low Method, Capoeira, and Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu. Moreover, the course will work with improvisation techniques, and students will be guided through a series of practical exercises. These exercises, similar to those in a regular dance class, address technical and performance issues such as alignment, connection,  balance, transition, and discovery, empowering full expression through the body.

Brazilian Arts Fusion Dance is a physical-based course. Therefore, students are expected to physically engage in exercises during class time, be open to repetition, and learn dance phrases.
